Get the support, tools, and information you need to be safe

You should not spy on other people. The cameras are not allowed in your listing unless they are previously disclosed and visible, these are never permitted in private rooms such as bathrooms or sleeping areas. Do not access others’ accounts without authorization or violate others’ privacy, copyrights etc.

Keeping yourself, your payment and your personal information are protected by staying on our secured platform throughout the entire process from communication, to booking and payment. You should not provide credit card information in another platform to avoid getting scammed.
Get the phone numbers you need if someone is in danger or injured.

The Let n’Go community members share their homes, neighborhoods, and experiences. If you’re opening your home as a host or experiencing a host’s hospitality as a guest, you need to feel safe and secured to trust anyone. We ask of you to respect others’ property, information, and personal properties.

Do not take property that isn’t yours or use someone’s belongings without their permission, copy others’ keys or any identity documents, damage others’ properties, remain in listings after a stay is concluded. or threaten anyone with giving a bad ratings or any other penalty or harm to obtain compensation or other benefits.

You should not make transactions outside of Let n’Go payments system, commit booking fraud, credit card fraud, or launder money, attempt to drive traffic to other sites or market unrelated products, diverting payments meant for others, abusing our referrals system or making a false claim against the other members of our community.
Violating the other privacy or intellectual property rights
Learn about Let N\' Go Trust and Safety
Every night, millions of people stay in homes on Let n\' Go in cities all over the world.
Safe tips for choosing a place

Traveling around means spending your own time and hard-earned money. So, you will want to be sure to find a place that suits you perfectly. These are some guides to assist you in your travel with confidence, knowing that you’ve made the right decisions, you will not worry anymore.

Get exactly what you’re looking for by using our search filters, like price, home type, and amenities. You need to make sure that you’ve read the host’s profile or experience description and paying attention to the amenities, house rules or Travel requirements, and the cancellation policy or procedures.
Looking through feedback from the past guests can you help find the right fit for you. You will the see ratings on detailed reviews with feedback about the experience.
The Guests can only leave feedback after they’ve stayed with the specific host, The feedback you’re seeing is based on actual experiences.

Let n’Go has secure messaging tool that is a safe and easy way for you to ask the potential host about any questions you have about their home before you book. After you finished booking, you can also message your host to stay in touch throughout your trip.
Always communicate & pay on Let n\'Go

Once you’ve arrived to your destined location, you need to make sure you know where all relevant emergency equipment and safety information is located. If you’re not sure where something like the first aid kit or fire extinguisher is, don not hesitate to ask your host about it. It is better to be always prepared before you travel.

Even if you’re traveling using our Let n’Go mobile app or not, it’s always a good idea to research your destination ahead of time to check with your local embassy in case there are any travel warnings or other requirements.
In an emergency, or if your personal safety is threatened, contact local police or emergency services immediately.
Your Let n’Go experience begins the moment you embrace adventure. It will only be possible when you trust our community and feel safe.
The listing you provide should let the potential guests know about the unique features and amenities of your home. This will help your guests to have an idea about you and your area.

If you want to know more about your guest before accepting their reservation request, check out their profile. The Hosts and guests can only review each other after a reservation is complete, so the feedback you’re reading is based on actual experiences.

Make sure you relay your house common rules to your guests. You may need to notify your neighbors that you will have guests, and remind guests not to bother your neighbors, you can make specific expectations (like quiet hours) in your house rules.

Every guest is asked to provide their Correct full name, date of birth, phone number, email address and payment information to Let n’Go before booking. Home hosts also have the option to require guests to provide Let n’Go with any government ID before booking their listing

Our Let n’Go provides a secure messaging tool that gives you the chance to get to know guests and answer or ask any questions. Messaging is a great place to communicate things like check-in or provide local recommendations.
To prevent any surprises, you may want to include the information covered above in your House Rules in your Let n’Go listing profile.

Do not commit physical or sexual assault, sexual abuse, sexual harassment, domestic violence, robbery, human trafficking, or any other acts of violence, or hold anyone against their will. Members of dangerous organizations, including terrorist, organized criminal, and violent racist groups, we do not welcome this kind of organizations. Let n’Go is committed to working with law enforcement as appropriate and responding to valid law enforcement requests.

You need to remind your guests about keeping noise down. You may consider if you will allow babies, pets, or parties. Develop a policy about guests inviting other people over, and ensure your guests are clear about your “policy.”
Do not convey an intent to harm anyone by your words or any physical actions. We take threats of self-harm as seriously as we do actions and may intervened if we become aware of the threat.
Do not keep unsecured weapons, disease risks, or dangerous animals, nor should you create conditions that increase the likelihood of a fire, delay or prevent escape in the event of emergency.
If you allow pets, make sure your guests are educated about things like local parks and local customs (cleaning up after your dog).

Make sure you equip your home and your guests with the safety essentials they might need during their trip. This includes things like a working smoke and a fire extinguisher, a first aid kit, and information on how to get in touch with local authorities.
These are the tips on how you can help to ensure your hosting, and your guest’s trip, goes off without a problem.
If you do not allow smoking, we suggest posting a sign to remind your guests. If you do allow smoking, ensure you have an ashtray available in smoking areas.
Make sure you tell them the parking rules for your building and neighborhood to your guests.
